The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Custody death cuffs
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Custody death cuffs
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Amal Kanti Das, a former sub-inspector, and Sunil Biswas, the inspector-in-charge of Bally police station, were sent to four and two years in jail and fined Rs 50,000 and Rs 20,000, respectively, by a Howrah court in connection with the death of an accused in custody on February 25, 2002.         
	According to the prosecution, Netai Das, a resident of Madhubati in Hooghly, was arrested for theft. He was in the lock-up for six days and tortured by the officers.        
	Eden trains: Eastern Railway will run two special trains on Thursday for spectators to return home after the India-Sri Lanka match at Eden Gardens. The BBD Bag-Baruipur special, via Majherhat-Ballygunge, will leave Eden Gardens station at 11.10pm and the Prinsep Ghat-Naihati special via Dum Dum junction, at 11.34pm.         
	Suicide: Ucharan Roy, a 27-year-old lifer, hanged himself in Alipore jail early on Tuesday. Police said he was suffering from depression.        
	Mishap: Taxi driver Raju Majumdar and passenger Bappa Chandra were injured after the brakes failed and the vehicle rammed into a bus near the Moulali crossing on Tuesday, police said. The two were taken to NRS hospital.                                                                                                                                                          
